Name: A Worried Mother
Flavor Text: I've looked everywhere!
On Visit: If this Explorer has visited Lost Child, upgrade to Happy Reunion

Name: Abandoned Wagon
Flavor Text: Deep wagon ruts make it impossible to lose the way.

Name: Airlock
Flavor Text: An airlock with simple controls: two buttons labeled 'Depart' and 'Seal'. Until recently, it has never been used.
On Reveal Text: For a year, the airlock out of Stratohaven has stood unlocked, yet none dared venture beyond. Our haven in the clouds has provided all we needed. Why risk the barren lands below? But today, something changed. In the distance, bursts of light pierced the sky - fireworks, akin to those in our old TV shows. Are we truly alone? Curiosity stirs in Stratohaven. Our bravest will journey to uncover this enigma.

Name: Bandit Copse
Flavor Text: The locals know to stay away from this stand of trees, but traveler's can't tell it from any other.
Ability: Insert any tile to not lose a tile when visiting. Insert a Woods tile to upgrade to a Forest.
On Visit: Remove the tile in the first slot of the journey plan
OnVisitPopupText: Oh no! Bandits stole one of your explorer's cards!

Name: Barren Earth
Flavor Text: The ashy regolith of this place offers no comfort.

Name: Bonefire
Flavor Text: Exhausted refugees huddle around a mound of burning bones and warn each other about the dangers they've encountered.
Ability: Insert one Wood to deck 5 cards and 7 Wastelands and upgrade to Smouldering Bonefire

Name: Briar Passage
Ability: Insert a forest tile to clear the passageway.
Secret Effect: Ability upgrades to Cleared Briar Passage

Name: Bristling Wall
Ability: Impassable. Insert Wasteland to burn the thicket.

Name: Canopy Village
Ability: Insert a forest, 50% chance to deck a Settlement, 50% chance to deck any card.

Name: Cleared Briar Passage
On Reveal: Place adjacent Nettled Nest. Place an adjacent Bristling Wall.

Name: Cleared Thorngate
On Reveal: Place adjacent Briar Passage. Place 4 adjacent Bristling Walls

Name: Complex Foundation
Flavor Text: A complex foundation to some kind of structure. The Plasticom has instructed us not to disturb it.
Ability: Insert Stratolink to upgrade.

Name: Contagious Mangrove
On Visit: 30% chance to replace a tile in the Journey Plan with a Swamp

Name: Control Room
On Reveal Text: The coordinates lead us not to another city in the clouds, but to a secluded control room nestled on a lesser-known mountain. The room is filled with old technology and screens, some still flickering with life. Stasia's digital logs reveal she was a guardian of sorts, the most recent in a long line of clones, maintaining the technology that oversees these mountaintop settlements. The screens show several settlements like Stratohaven, yet ours is the only one with the gate marked 'open.' The question lingers in the air: If Stasia died before Stratohaven was unlocked, who unlocked our city, and why? We hope the Stratolink printplans we discovered will lead to answers.

Name: Creeping Fungus
Flavor Text: The sound the Stratohaven's fungal sweepers make when they encounter creeping fungus spores sounds like a mechanical cough, but the plasticom assures us this is just how recursive filtering sounds when it is functioning normally.
Secret Effect: Place Creeping Fungus in an adjacent unexplored tile every 60 seconds.

Name: Crow Throne
Flavor Text: On this throne sits a pessimistic oracle.
Ability: Reveals a random card in the Journey Plan.
Secret Effect: The revealed random card is on the low end of the spectrum of effects. It is revealed to be worse than the average effect of that biome.

Name: Crystal Clear River
Flavor Text: Like flowing glass.

Name: Database Protein Printer
Flavor Text: Today's Menu: Breakfast Bacon flavored protein porridge. Lunch Special! Chicken breast protein porridge. Dinner: Oatsimilie Protein Porridge.
Ability: Insert Woods to upgrade to Hydroponic Protein Printer.

Name: Delta
On Visit: Move to an adjacent Spreading Delta

Name: Electronic Diary
On Reveal: Unlocks Pool 3, Deck 4 cards, Show Stasia's Residency tile on other side of Purification Plant Maintenance Slough
On Reveal Text: The device Bennett found indeed turned out to be an electronic diary, and it belonged to someone named Stasia. According to the diary, she lived in a place that sounds remarkably like our own Stratohaven. She mentions coordinates that she often visited. Maybe we can find her.

Name: Endless Festival
Flavor Text: The original Explorer has found love and settled with a local!
Ability: Insert a field to attend, deck a field. Insert a forest to attend, deck a forest. Insert a swamp to attend, deck a swamp.

Name: Explorer's Gate
Flavor Text: In 12 foot tall letters, 'Curiosity' is las-etched on the inside of the gate,  and 'Wonder' on the outside.

Name: Fireworks
Ability: Insert a tile to Upgrade to Fireworks Glenn

Name: Fireworks Glen
On Reveal: Deck 4 cards, Show Strider Village tile 1 space away, increase journey plan slots
On Reveal Text: Our expedition below Stratohaven yielded the unimaginable – survivors! We believed the surface world extinct, yet here they thrive, ignorant of our technologies like protein printers or television screens. Among the survivors, they exclaim that our technology reminds them of 'talking metal' that their neighbor speaks of. They provide directions to their village, where tales of this device originated. Perhaps this is a clue to others from our world.

Name: Friendly Tavern
Flavor Text: All who are weary are welcome to rest here and hear the tales of fellow travelers.
Ability: Insert a card to deck 1 card

Name: Froggie Bog Pirates
Flavor Text: A twangy dirge drifts through the miasma acompanied by a croaking chrous that reveals a submerged stash.
Ability: Impassable.
On Reveal: Explorer is turned back, reveal Submerged Stash 2 hexes away.

Name: Gastroprint Farm
Flavor Text: Today's Menu: Breakfast Savory Cinnamon Oat Crepes, Lunch Special! Five Star Chicken Tikka Masala, Dinner: Maple Glazed Pancetta Charcuterie

Name: Giant Spider Lair
Flavor Text: insert wasteland, 30% chance to pass, insert fields 50% chance to pass, insert settlement for 90% chance to pass.

Name: Global Datamentarian
Flavor Text: The Plasticom voraciously records all the updated information we bring it from outside Stratohaven.

Name: Grassland
Flavor Text: Like a lawn the runs to the horizon.
Ability: Insert any tile to upgrade to Grassland Highway.

Name: Grassland Highway
Flavor Text: Printer drones have spread this spindle of mountaintop plasphalt all the way to the horizon.

Name: Graveyard Crest
Flavor Text: Six gravestones worn smooth with time fill this small memorial. Five of them stand above gaping pits.
Ability: Insert a field to fill in the pits. Insert a wasteland to remove this desecration.
Secret Effect: Inserting a wasteland upgrades to Vengeful Vantage, decks 5 wastelands. Insert a field upgrades to Barren Earth.

Name: Green Canopy
Flavor Text: Wind ripples an emerald ceiling, causing slivers of sunlight to dance across the carpet of ferns.
Ability: Insert a Settlement to upgrade to Canopy Village, Insert a Field to upgrade to Megalo Fruit Farm

Name: Highland Plateau
Flavor Text: Grazing animals have worn a thick path into the turf here.

Name: Honored Court
Flavor Text: Uh, you know what. We'll take you there ourselves.
Ability: Knights escort your explorer safely to the next waypoint. Skip effects on the way.

Name: Hydroponic Protein Printer
Flavor Text: Today's Menu: Breakfast: Whole Grain Chia Oats. Lunch Special! Bacon Protein BLT. Dinner: Chicken Salad With Celery.
Ability: Insert Swamp to upgrade to Gastroprint Farm

Name: Landmark
Flavor Text: Did the ancient world use this spire as a point of reference? No other purpose is apparent.
On Reveal: Reduce the chance to get lost on all adjacent tiles by 20%

Name: Lodestone Outcropping
Flavor Text: The knowledge required to make compasses was never lost to us, but on our tiny mountaintop, there was no need for them.
On Visit: Explorers visiting here reduce their chance to get lost by 5%

Name: Lost Child
Ability: Insert a tile to check on the child, deck a card. (maybe make 5 of these, one for each type so the deck is the same biome you spent)
On Reveal: Place A Worried Mother 3 tiles away

Name: Lunar Vantage Array
Flavor Text: A 10,000 year old communication array is ready to recieve one last update from the Lunar Vantage Point Base. But what is it pointed at?
Ability: Insert Swamp to reduce the chance of being lost in all placed tiles by 4%, upgrade to Silent Array.

Name: Megalo Fruit Farm
Flavor Text: Each Megalofruit is as big as a man. Getting them down from the lofty canopy is a challenge.

Name: Merchant Shack
Flavor Text: An old man lives here
On Visit: Your explorer trades a tile for magic beans. Upgrade to Tattered Shack.

Name: Nettled Nest
Ability: Insert a tile to deck 1 wasteland, 6 woods, 4 Settlements, 2 Fields. Upgrades to Ball of Nettles

Name: Pale Hall
Flavor Text: Color seeps out of this place until even skin is white with shock.
On Visit: Add a Journey Plan stop to a random AdjacentDistance=2 tile

Name: Pine Forest
Flavor Text: The plasticom tells us that the only biome more swarming with life than a forest is the ocean. But who among us has seen the sea?

Name: Plasticom
Flavor Text: The immortal intelligent computer that has kept Stratohaven running for 10,000 years.
Ability: Insert a Woods to upgrade to Global Datamentarian.

Name: Predatory Distillery
Flavor Text: Well… at least it was a good time.
Secret Effect: Teleport the explorer to a random explored tile within 5 tiles.
On Visit: Explorer gets drunk and awakens… somewhere.

Name: Purification Plant Maintenance Overflow
Flavor Text: A perfect water recycler, in 10,000 years it has not lost a drop.
Ability: Impassable. Insert Swamp to upgrade to The Great River Of Beyond

Name: Quaint Village
Flavor Text: This tranquil collection of cottages must conceal something more sinister.
Ability: Insert a tile to investigate!
Secret Effect: Your explorer is still there. Investigate ability upgrades to Wedding Festival

Name: Quicksand
Ability: Insert a tile, 50% chance for all Explorers to move to an adjacent tile.
On Visit: Explorers on this tile cannot leave.

Name: Riparian Glade
Ability: Impassable. Insert a woods to pass and deck a woods.

Name: Robot Buddha
Flavor Text: Nearly as old as the Stratohaven, the Robot Buddha has learned to live sustainably in chaos. It wants nothing, it needs nothing.
Ability: None

Name: Roguish Smile
Flavor Text: A handsome rogue offers to show us the way, but there's something off about his smile.
On Reveal: Lose a tile, ignore the next tile effect.

Name: Seed Vault
Flavor Text: Every seed the last of its kind. We'll restore each linage to the world.
On Reveal: Deck a forest, field, and swamp.

Name: Silent Array
Flavor Text: A communcations array listening for a message that will never arrive. Scattered around the base of the array are images of the area from impossibly high above.

Name: Smiling Rogue
Flavor Text: A handsome rogue offers to show us the way, but the route is hard to remember.
On Reveal: Place a card from your hand on an adjacent space.

Name: Smokey Canyon
Flavor Text: *cough* *cough* *hack* *snuff* *gasp*

Name: Smouldering Bonefire
Flavor Text: Exhausted refugees huddle around a mound of burning bones and warn each other about the dangers they've encountered.

Name: Sprawling Hive City
Ability: insert field to place an adjacent settlement tile. If that was the only adjacent settlement tile, upgrade to hive city heart
On Reveal: place an adjacent settlement tile. If that was the only adjacent settlement tile or there are no ajacent spots, upgrade to hive city heart

Name: Spreading Delta
On Reveal: If next to a Spreading Delta, place 2 adjacent Delta Edges
On Visit: Move to an adjacent Delta Edge

Name: Stasia's Residency
On Reveal: Unlocks Pool 4, Deck 4 cards, reveals Control room far away
On Reveal Text: We found Stasia's home, but she has been dead for many years now. Her husband, now an old man, guards her possessions like precious treasures. From her computer, we extract the coordinates - they lead to a location that's not on any of our maps. It's time to explore these unknown coordinates and unravel the mysteries they hold.

Name: Stratolink
Flavor Text: An optical communication beam emitter, capable of transmitting terrabytes of data thousands of miles along line of sight in an instant.
Ability: Insert a tile to open a Stratohaven.
Secret Effect: Doesn't actually do anything aside from maybe keeping track of how many you've done.

Name: Strider Village
Ability: Unlocks Pool 2, Deck 2 woods and 2 forests, Show Electronic Device tile on other side of The Great Gate
OnVisitPopupText: In the village, we found the old man named Bennett. Known among his neighbors for his eccentric interests, Bennett claims he's been experimenting with a strange, beeping box he found buried near the village a decade ago. He insists it's not just scrap metal. His description sounds eerily similar to our old communication devices. Could it be a lost relic from another Stratohaven? We decide to investigate further, hoping to uncover a piece of our forgotten past. He provides the location of where he hid the diary.

Name: Submerged Stash
Flavor Text: The eclectic riches we found here may lead us back to their owners, but we should not return here once the theives discover what is missing.
Ability: Impassable. Insert Wood or Field to visit and deck 6 settlements. Upgrade to Sunken Stash.

Name: Sunken Stash
Ability: Impassable.

Name: Tattered Shack
Flavor Text: No one lives here.
Ability: None

Name: Temple of Saint Bread
Flavor Text: After a cup of matcha latte, everything in life looks a little better.
Ability: Reveals your card to be a positive effect
Secret Effect: The revealed random card is on the upper end of the spectrum of effects. It is revealed to be better than the average effect of that biome.

Name: The Great Gate
Flavor Text: Sealed against the cataclysm for 10,000 years.
Ability: Impassable. Insert forest to upgrade to Explorer's Gate.

Name: The Great River Of Beyond
Flavor Text: Now we take in sludge, and give the world a crystal clear river.
On Reveal: Plus 1 Explorer, Place adjacent Crystal Clear River

Name: Thorngate
Flavor Text: Curtains of sharp briars grow so quickly they seem to move.
Ability: Insert a woods tile to clear the gateway.

Name: Toadstool Grove
Flavor Text: Towering toadstools shade the moist soil.
Ability: Insert a woods, deck 2 swamps

Name: Traveler's Forum
Flavor Text: Lectures, memoirs, and scientific illustrations inspire the next generation of explorer dreams.
Ability: Insert Wasteland to upgrade to World Academy.

Name: Triple Vortex
Flavor Text: I’ve a feeling we’re not in Kansas anymore.
Secret Effect: Your explorer gets lost 100% of the time.

Name: Tumbling River
Flavor Text: Water tumbles head over heals down a thousand feet.

Name: Unpassable
Flavor Text: Too steep to climb.
Ability: Impassable

Name: Vengeful Vantage
Flavor Text: Whistling wails haunt this hillock, whether by wraiths or the wind.
On Reveal: Increase lost chance in all surrounding tiles 20%

Name: Videonarium
Flavor Text: A crowd has gathered to complete the 9853rd Annual Series Marathon of Friends
Ability: insert forest to upgrade to Traveler's Forum.

Name: Village
Flavor Text: Somehow these people have found a way to survive in 10,000 years of cataclysm.

Name: Wagon Caravan
Flavor Text: These nomads have seen a hundred lands, but when they hear about the mountaintop, they promise to visit soon.
Ability: Insert a tile to deck 4 settlements, 4 fields, 4 forests, and 1 swamp. Upgrade to Wagon Ruts

Name: Waterfall
Flavor Text: Mountain meets valley in a plume of mist.

Name: Wedding Festival
Flavor Text: The original Explorer has found love and settled with a local!
Ability: Insert a field to attend, deck a field. Insert a forest to attend, deck a forest. Insert a swamp to attend, deck a swamp. Upgrade to Endless festival
On Reveal: Place the tiles that were lost by the previous explorer
On Visit: A wedding guest loved your toast so much they joined! Plus 1 explorer!

Name: Wetland
Flavor Text: Not for us, but the birds seem to enjoy it.

Name: Wildfire
On Reveal: Upgrade adjacent Bristling Walls to Wildfire. Upgrade to Barren Earth

Name: Winding Tunnel
Flavor Text: Where does this go?
Ability: Skip the effects of the next tile.

Name: Winewater Spring
Flavor Text: Unbelievable stories of a land long lost are told here. Something about these myths makes you believe they were once real.
Secret Effect: None. This is a reference to the game Where The Water Tastes Like Wine, a strong influence on this game.

Name: Wolf Copse
Flavor Text: The goats know to stay away from this stand of trees, but traveler's can't tell it from any other.
Ability: Insert any tile to not lose a tile when visiting. Insert a Woods tile to upgrade to a Forest.

Name: Woods
Flavor Text: The plasticom tells us that the only biome more swarming with life than a forest is the ocean. But who among us has seen the sea?

Name: World Academy
Flavor Text: Shocked by the dangers of a chaotic world, we systemitized prepartions for all explorers.

Name: zzDebug
Flavor Text: This is the biome for debug testing cards.

Name: zzDEBUG Draw 1 Card On Place
Flavor Text: This tile adds a card to your deck when you place it.

Name: zzDEBUG Draw 10 Cards
Flavor Text: This card's ability takes any card and adds 10 cards to your deck.

Name: zzDebug Place 1 Adjacent
Flavor Text: This tile places 1 adjacent grasslands no more than distance 1.

Name: zzDEBUG Place 9 Adjacent
Flavor Text: This tile places 9 adjacent grasslands on unexplored tiles no more than 2 adjacency distance away.

Name: zzDEBUG Remove All Plan Tiles
Flavor Text: This card removes all the tiles in the Journey plan, leaving empty slots to the existing destinations.

Name: zzDEBUG Remove First Plan Tile
Flavor Text: This card removes the first tile in the Journey plan, leaving an empty slot to the existing destination.

Name: zzDebug Remove Last Plan Tile
Flavor Text: This card removes the last tile in the Journey plan, leaving an empty slot to the existing destination.

Name: zzDebug Remove Random Plan Tile
Flavor Text: This card removes a random tile in the Journey plan, leaving an empty slot to the existing destination.

Name: Wagon Ruts
Flavor Text: Signs of travelers that passed through here

Name: zzDEBUG Place Random Swamp
Flavor Text: This tile places a random swamp adjacent to this tile when placed.
